review_blob: This is damn fine beer. Tons of oak, vanilla, and bitter-sweet malt flavors. There is a faint hit of cinnamon, however it is slightly lost in the mix. Not nearly as heavy as many other barrel aged imperial stouts, which is kind of nice, but the flavor is just as full.
Very straight forward west coast-style IPA with tons of citrus and pine. Light and neutral malt body.
Juicy and bright with some tangerine notes. A very piney / result finish. Very good, but would like to try again.
Sweet and citrusy IPA with a slightly grassy finish. A bit sweet for my liking, but still a tasty beer.
Tart, dark malt, raspberry, and light chocolate. Very acidic, but nice. Would have again.

If I drank this blind, I would thing it was one of Southern Tiers typical sugar bombs. It is incredibly sweet, aromatic / perfumy, and slightly artificial in flavor. The vanilla, chocolate, and coffee flavors are very strong, but not in a well balanced fashion.
Tons of oak, roasty notes, and coffee. Very sweet and slightly nutty. A bit of a sugar bomb.
beer_name: Fremont Dark Star - Bourbon Barrel Coffee Edition

review_blob: Sugar bomb, but delicious. Strong blackberry / cherry flavor with some slight saltiness in the finish. Drinks a bit like a Manhattan with nice rye, fruit, and bitter flavors.
beer_name: Goose Island Bourbon County Stout - Regal Rye Barrel

review_blob: Tons of melon and pine with some light citrus. Light green pepper flavor which is a bit odd.
Very juicy and mildly sweet with notes of citrus, strawberry, and cotton candy. A nice occasional IPA, but wouldn't be a regular for me.
beer_name: West Flanders / Elysian of Boom!!! IPA

review_blob: Fantastic IPA with tons of citrus, and some slight pine. Very balanced, crisp, and not sweet. Has a light breadiness in the after taste.
Not bad, not great. Just a blue collar pale ale done well. Slightly citrus hops, bready yeast, and light malt body.
Tons of oak, nice tartness, and nice caramel notes. Very complex and balanced. Not too dry, not too sweet. Highly carbed.
Wow. Very good. Tons of citrus - particularly tangerine. Some slight grass, but not too much. Clean and balanced.
beer_name: Holy Mountain Mosaic Extra Pale Ale

review_blob: Fairly sweet with some nice citrus zest. Light bodied and in color, but tons of flavor.
Very complex with nice oak, funk, and cereal with some light tartness and citrus and grass.
A pretty good IPA with great citrus and tropical notes. A slight marshmallow yeast flavor that isn't my favorite, but it is very subtle.
Nice classic stout with light coffee and chocolate. The coffee is extremely roasty and the cocoa nibs are very subtle. Not a bad brew and a nice break from extreme beers.
beer_name: Fremont Codename S.T.O.U.T. - Cacao Nibs & Coffee

review_blob: Tons of malty cereal with some slight bourbon notes. Needs more time in the barrel in my opinion.
Light and extremely grassy. Not much else to say about this one. Not quite as good as their other IPAs.
Terrible wet dog aftertaste, but the funky and earthy tartness is nice while it lasts.
Very nice full bodied stout with hints of coffee and dark chocolate. Slight oatmeal bitterness which balances it out.
Tons of citrus, particularly candied orange peel and tangerine. Slightly sweet, but not overbearing.
Funky and earthy with slight tartness and a rider like fruitiness. Light in body and flavor.
This is a very tasty beer with flavors of cinnamon, coconut, oak, vanilla, and caramel. Sweet, but incredibly good.
This is a great IPA that is incredibly balance. Tons of citrus and tropical hop notes with a slight pine finish. Not too sweet which is nice.
Very fruity IPA with tons of peach and pineapple. Slightly sweet, but not overly so.
Slightly roasty notes with cherry like tartness. Very unique. Has some slight funk that adds depth to an already interesting brew.
Sticky sweet with very nice floral and citrus aroma and flavor. Some light grassy notes in the finish. Good, but perhaps too sweet to drink very much of.

Admittedly I usually hate black IPAs. With that noted, this is not a bad beer. I really like how the maple sweetness and vanilla notes work with the malt backbone of this beer. The hops are mostly aromatic, though still hoppier than I would like.
Very nice hop profile that is full of tropical and peach notes. The actual peach flavor is minimal and perhaps highlight the hop flavors. Slightly sweet, but otherwise great.
beer_name: Stone / 4 Hands / Bale Breaker Sorry Not Sorry

review_blob: Not bad, but my least favorite offering from Blackberry Farm. Like a stout pitched with saison yeast. Has roasty flavors and hints of chocolate and biscuit. The yeast offers some fruity esters and light bubblegum.
Thin, nutty, and only hints of oak. Kind of a weak beer in my opinion. Very bready / yeasty.

Sweet and creamy with strong vanilla and coconut flavors. Was hosing for perhaps a bit more depth, but it is a tasty beer none the less. The vanilla and coconut kind of come off like flavored tobacco.
beer_name: Oskar Blues / Shamrock Death By Coconut

review_blob: Yeasty, roasty, and hints of chocolate and espresso. Not really digging this one.

Nice roasted notes with slight coffee flavor. Has some slight tartness and sweetness from the cherries and some light vanilla / burnt sugar. Overall an enjoyable beer, but not something that is mind-blowing.
UPDATED: NOV 2, 2015
Very coffee forward with biscuit notes and only a hit of hops. Not bad if you're in the mood for a coffee beer that is slightly less heavy than a stout.
beer_name: Goose Island Fulton St. Blend Coffee Ale

review_blob: Tons of espresso aroma. Has nice flavors of chocolate and coffee this hints of apple, vanilla, and pecans. A great balanced brew with light sweetness and bitterness. Very good.
Very nutty with some slight vanilla and cocoa. Has some strong hazelnut flavor. Not really getting much bourbon or oak. A fairly light bodied stout.
Tart, but not overly so. Some wild cherry-like flavor. Wish that it had some more depth, but very tasty none-the-less.

A great example of a subtle and tasteful brew. Very light in flavor and body, but full of delicate flavor of flowers, orange peel, jasmine, and black tea. Has a light breadiness and some nice yeast flavor that is typical of a triple.
I dig this brewery, but this is not a very well constructed triple in my opinion. Tastes like a super sweet pale ale with some poorly pitched belgian yeast. Hints of popsicle sticks.
A really great pale ale. Nice cereal notes with bright citrus notes. Smooth, light, and crisp.

Not a bad beer, but not mindblowing either. The barrel / oak is very faint and not really at all as vanilla / caramel -like as I would want. The triple is very bright with some lemon aroma and a slight peppercorn flavor. Has some obvious bubblegum-belgian-style-yeast notes.
A really solid brew that isnt too heavy, sticky, or sweet. It is rather light and crisp with some cereal shining through. Has some nice tropical and citrus notes with some light pine.
Sweet, roasty, and some slightly tart and metallic notes. Tastes a bit oxidized. Not a ton of bourbon or maple notes present.
beer_name: Dark Horse 6 Pairs of Legs Maple Porter

review_blob: Slightly sweet with some piney bitterness to balance it out. Has some really nice caramel flavors, molasses, maple syrup, and some slight dark fruit. Not overly sweet.

Tons of floral and citrus aroma on the nose. Has a really nice citrus and pine flavor with some slight earthiness. The finish is a little grassy, but not overly so. A great IPA and will likely be a go to in my fridge.

This tastes like a home brewer trying to brew a DIPA and throwing too much specialty malt into the grain bill. Tons of caramel and slight rye flavor. The hop profile is spicy and tropical with a really bitter aftertaste.
beer_name: Founders Backstage Series #13: reDANKulous Imperial Red IPA
